text: This afternoon, I toured the control tower, viewed the radar system, & joined a roundtable at @INDairport w @RepAndreCarson & @RepBarragan to learn more about how #Indianapolis' investments in aviation infrastructure are helping the local economy & creating jobs. #MakeItInAmerica https://t.co/FoZmk3Uakn

I heard time and time again today that investing in infrastructure is good for business. Local community leaders called on the federal government to remain involved in infrastructure as technology shifts. 7/7

I heard from community members doing a study on sustainability, resiliency, & the city’s vulnerabilities when it comes to climate change, & that Congress should look at what the country can do to prepare our infrastructure for the future rather than reacting to last disaster. 6/7
Another concern raised today in #Indy was about aging water and sewer infrastructure, a problem we see across the country. 5/7

Participants also discussed how infrastructure can help alleviate poverty so more people can #MakeItInAmerica. Improved public transit provides lower cost transit options & jobs that can help Americans get out of poverty. 4/7
I heard public-private partnerships aren't a panacea. The debt from investments must be paid back, it’s not free money. 3/7
The @WhiteHouse infrastructure proposal asks for 80% of funding to come from local communities. I heard a unanimous "no" from the community when I asked if that was workable. 2/7

Today's #MakeItInAmerica #ListeningTour stop in #Indianapolis focused on infrastructure, which is key to creating jobs and strengthening our economic competitiveness. Here are some of my takeaways from the discussion with local leaders. 1/7

On Saturday, I toured @nrec_cmu w @USRepMikeDoyle & learned about entrepreneurship & robotics technology. We heard on the #ListeningTour that embracing innovation and rapidly changing technology will be key to ensuring businesses & workers can #MakeItInAmerica. https://t.co/jVCERxVDzU

On the #MakeItInAmerica #ListeningTour, I joined @RepAndreCarson & @RepBarragan for a ride on the @IndyGoBus, the largest fleet of electric buses in the country. Local officials discussed how investments in new transit systems has helped create local jobs. https://t.co/Yhk01ZSh2n

Good morning from Indianapolis, our final city on this #MakeItInAmerica #ListeningTour. This morning I am joined by @RepAndreCarson & @RepBarragan at the @IndyGoBus Center for a conversation with community leaders about infrastructure successes & challenges in #Indy. https://t.co/2bcVM4jIuT

With technology always changing, it’s important that workers have access to skills training throughout their careers. Roundtable participants said Congress can take steps to ensure that workers have access to continuing training so our workforce can stay competitive. 7/7

Another concern was that training for new skills is often expensive. What role can Congress play in ensuring that American workers have access to affordable skills training? One recommendation was investing in these programs instead of cutting them. 6/7
An interesting challenge brought up more than once at the education roundtable this morning is that children are presented with college as the only path post-high school. How can we change that? 5/7
In Toledo, I heard we ought to embrace technology and that we shouldn’t fear automation because American workers should build the robots that businesses will use. 4/7

Roundtable participants pointed out the best workers aren't always the best trainers. One suggestion I heard was to create partnerships between manufacturers and educators to ensure we have strong teachers who can prepare students. 3/7
Right now, there are jobs open across the United States but our workers are not trained to fill these roles. How can we close that gap? 2/7

We had a great discussion this morning during the #MakeItInAmerica #ListeningTour in Toledo. We talked about the importance of ensuring that our workforce has the training necessary to be prepared for the jobs of the future. 1/7

On the #MakeItInAmerica #ListeningTour this morning, I am in Toledo, OH at @trainwithcts with @RepMarcyKaptur & @RepBarragan for a round table discussion on what we can do to close the skills gap & ensure all workers have the skills training for the next generation of jobs. https://t.co/VRCHGr8uXu
